ng first and last strokes, the mid-strokes reach down to the base-line; rho has a small eye, not always fully closed; alpha has broken bar; omega varies between open circle closed by horizontal bar and closed ovoid form with horizontal bar; phi has a small circular eye; sigma has standard form with horizontal top and bottom storkes; omicron is approximately the same size as other letters.",[208,212],{"type":39,"l":209,"from":41,"to":210,"h":211,"unit":43},"Lines 1-5","line5","30-45",{"type":45,"l":46,"from":41,"to":42,"unit":43},{"_":214,"notBefore":215,"notAfter":216,"precision":16},"2nd century BCE(?)",-200,-101,[218,219],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59,"offset":60},[221],[63,64],[223,224],38.06519,15.11438,{"_":155,"role":156,"ref":157},{"_":227,"type":160},"8706",{"_":162,"mainLang":163,"languages":229},[162],"492811",{"n":78,"url":232,"height":233,"width":234,"desc":235,"surfaceType":83},"ISic001207_tiled.tif","3212px","2498px","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas",[],[238,174,175,176,239,240,90],"Kaibel, 1890, IG","Manni Piraino, 1976, Contribution Épigraphique à l'Étude de l'esclavage en Sicile","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano",[178,179,94,180,242,243,96],"R9M263EA","RZSFKACR",[245,246,247,121,125,185,101,102,103,104,186,187,188,163],"isic001207","epitaph for nemeris, a goldsmith",{"_":10},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Νεμέριε̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>Γρανῶνι \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>Νυμφόδωρε \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>χρυσοχόε \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>χαῖρε \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\